      • getEGColorTransform

        public java.util.List<javax.xml.bind.JAXBElement<?>> getEGColorTransform()
        Gets the value of the egColorTransform property.

        This accessor method returns a reference to the live list, not a snapshot. Therefore any modification you make to the returned list will be present inside the JAXB object. This is why there is not a set method for the egColorTransform property.

        For example, to add a new item, do as follows: 

            getEGColorTransform().add(newItem);

        Objects of the following type(s) are allowed in the list JAXBElement<CTPercentage> JAXBElement<CTInverseGammaTransform> JAXBElement<CTPercentage> JAXBElement<CTPositiveFixedPercentage> JAXBElement<CTGrayscaleTransform> JAXBElement<CTComplementTransform> JAXBElement<CTInverseTransform> JAXBElement<CTPercentage> JAXBElement<CTPercentage> JAXBElement<CTPercentage> JAXBElement<CTPercentage> JAXBElement<CTAngle> JAXBElement<CTPercentage> JAXBElement<CTPercentage> JAXBElement<CTPercentage> JAXBElement<CTPercentage> JAXBElement<CTPositiveFixedPercentage> JAXBElement<CTPositiveFixedAngle> JAXBElement<CTPercentage> JAXBElement<CTPositiveFixedPercentage> JAXBElement<CTFixedPercentage> JAXBElement<CTPercentage> JAXBElement<CTPercentage> JAXBElement<CTPercentage> JAXBElement<CTPositivePercentage> JAXBElement<CTPositivePercentage> JAXBElement<CTGammaTransform> JAXBElement<CTPercentage>
